The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Sunday, May 30, 2004 				 Fleeing truck crushes child and aunt 
 A STAFF REPORTER 																								Calcutta, May 29: A woman and her three-year-old niece were crushed to death by a truck at Chitpore in north Calcutta while trying to flee after knocking them off a rickshaw. 																								Minutes after the incident, irate residents thrashed the helper of the truck. The driver fled. 																								Police said the mishap took place on Khagen Chatterjee Road when Kanchani Das, 40, and little Juin were headed for the Sarbamangala Ghat to take the ferry to their Bally residence. 																								The truck, which was coming out of a godown, hit the rickshaw while taking a turn. Kanchani and Juin fell on the road. The truck driver did not stop because, it seems, he wanted to flee, said an official of traffic departments fatal squad wing. The woman and the child were crushed under the rear wheels of the truck.																								When a few people gathered in protest, the driver jumped out of his cabin and fled. Their anger was then turned on the helper, who was rescued by the police in an unconscious state. He has been admitted to R.G. Kar Hospital in a critical condition. 
